		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">A hunting guide for those lost warriors....<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Aug 21st 9:48 AM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=96686568631662&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=96686568631662&num=0&post=1&replyto=96686568631662"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=96686568631662></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.25]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Warriors listen up because this could help you if your starting........<br>First off you choose your race in my opinon they all turn out the same in the long run....my warrior is a barbarien for instance.<br>Lets talk hunting!<br>I use the 2h slash it's up to you what you use but in my opinon as well 2h slashing is pretty damn good.Starting visit that guild you read about in the note and get the starting tunic ...equip all your items and get your butt out to that newbie field and hunt!<br>My experience is freeport so I will share with you about that. Once your level 3 don't waste time in the newbie parts at west freeport go to east freeport barley anyone there or just go on out to north ro and hunt by FP entrence it's nice exp. At 4 being a warrior with good hp's I think you can take a jackal even tho they are yellow. Take risk cause later you won't be as lucky to be able to do this. Now hunt in nro till level 7 .....I belive it was jackals and orc raiders....steer clear of those snakes they posion and thats very bad for a warrior with no cleric to aid him/her. At 7 I went to faydark and found the bandits there will level you to 8 pretty fast it's up to you if you would wanna stay but I recomend heading on back to ro and work on soloing scarabs....not spiders those posion as well even if you kill it and have very little hp its a good chance they will kill you in the long run. At level 9 it's group time! Get in a Dervish Cutthroat group in nro there are 3 camps so shouldn't be hard to find one that will need you. Do cutthroats till about 13 or 14....now head to Oasis of Marr which is the next zone over. Hunt Caiman and Crocs no deepwater stuff untill a lil bit higher.....stay in oasis till about 20 guys I don't care if it's boring or sumthin. Now at 20 take a long walk or short GG to North Karana and go to South Karana.....when you get to South Karana walk straight from the bridge don't stop untill you come to the Aviak City of ask for a guide there. Hunt here until 24 or 25.....now here comes the fun parts and where the money starts to increase.Go to Cazic Thule you can go through GG from a wizard or you can go ahead and walk through lake rathe and rathe mountain&nbsp;&nbsp;into ferrot...be careful of those guards.....and right in ferrot will be Cazic Thule.Alot of trains run through here so beware to get outta the way if ones on it's way there.Head straight out into the courtyard and take a left at the double door to the single door...when you walk in there head right and through that single door leading too Tae and Tower groups....at 25 I think you have the right to get on list for both....untill your called just talk to friends or get a small group and pull lizzys from the maze. Do tae untill about level 30 or so then do a lil of tower untill 32 or so....then I RECOMEND! the green pool group it's hard to explain to you how to get to it so it's best to ask someone while in the game=)....hunt here untill you reach 35 then head to upper zig group ask for a guide here and I recomend you get an invis before venturing into the maze to find it.Also at 35 you can leave Cazic-Thule again go to Lavastorm Mountains. In Lavastorm you can find Solusek Dungeon B. Find the tiger group there and get on the list.....and warriors....they may want you to pull for em so I would recomend you learn it one day it's not too hard to accomplish=)......Hunt here untill 45 or go ahead and break 45 here.....Currently I am 45=)<br>It's a tuff one but then again arn't all levels?<br>Along the way I don't mention getting the armor but your gonna need to on the way.....just keep that in mind and save that money for your Crafted Armor your gonna need it at 45 I am in crafted armor and a treeweave.Playing on Mithaniel Marr it's hard to be a newbie nowadays so many twinkies running around it's not even fun I pray day to day that we will get a server split I wanna go so bad........By the way I am Tacisio Bon'Vardi if you wanna stop by on Mith Marr throw me a tell=) <br>P.S. <br>I am poor right now so I can't twink you......sorry!!!!!</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=1><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=1&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=96686568631662&num=0&post=1&mid=96686568631662><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">0 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class1">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
